The evolutionary origins of 
 Nigella species are presumably in the Aegean and the adjacent Western-Irano-Turanian region; its centre of species diversity (
 Zohary, 1983; 
 Bittkau and Comes, 2009). The genus is found as wild in southern Europe, Russia, northern Africa, Asia Minor, Turkey, Middle-East, India, Pakistan, and Bangladesh (
 Tonçer and Kizil, 2004; 
 Zohary, 1983; 
 Dönmez and Mutlu, 2004; 
 Heiss and Oeggl, 2005; 
 Sharma et al., 2009; 
 Iqbal et al., 2010; 
 Heiss et al., 2011; 
 Rabbani et al., 2011; 
 Zhao et al., 2013; 
 Hossan et al., 2018).
